import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['speed'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    ax.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], c=data['dir'], cmap='hsv', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_title('How does wind direction vary across different locations?')
    plt.colorbar()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    dirCat_count = data['dirCat'].value_counts()
    dirCat_count.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common wind direction category across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=dirCat_count.max(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend([f'Most common wind direction category: {dirCat_count.idxmax()} ({dirCat_count.max():.2f})'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
